{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id60317d94-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58","identifier":"/us/usc/t30/s1224"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1224"},"text":"§ 1224.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Duties of Secretary","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id60317d95-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58","identifier":"/us/usc/t30/s1224/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Consulting with other agencies; prescribing rules and regulations; furnishing advice and assistance; coordinating research","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary, acting through the Director of the United States Bureau of Mines, shall administer this subchapter and, after full consultation with other interested Federal agencies, shall prescribe such rules and regulations as may be necessary to carry out its provisions. The Secretary shall furnish such advice and assistance as will best promote the purposes of this subchapter, shall participate in coordinating research initiated under this subchapter by the institutes, shall indicate to them such lines of inquiry that seem most important, and shall encourage and assist in the establishment and maintenance of cooperation by and between the institutes and between them and other research organizations, the United States Department of the Interior, and other Federal establishments.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id60317d96-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58","identifier":"/us/usc/t30/s1224/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Annual ascertainment of compliance","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"On or before the first day of July in each year beginning after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-08-29"},"text":"August 29, 1984","children":[],"tail":", the Secretary shall ascertain whether the requirements of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t30/s1223/a"},"text":"section 1223(a) of this title","children":[],"tail":" have been met as to each institute and State."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id60317d97-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/409/s4"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–409, § 4","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-08-29"},"text":"Aug. 29, 1984","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/98/1538"},"text":"98 Stat. 1538","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/483/s6"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–483, § 6","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-10-12"},"text":"Oct. 12, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/2340"},"text":"102 Stat. 2340","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/285/s10/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–285, § 10(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-05-18"},"text":"May 18, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/172"},"text":"106 Stat. 172","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id60317d98-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id60317d99-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id60317d9a-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c) of this section, which required the Secretary to make an annual report to Congress on the receipts, expenditures, and work of the institutes in all States under the provisions of this subchapter, terminated, effective ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-05-15"},"text":"May 15, 2000","children":[],"tail":", pursuant to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/66/s3003"},"text":"section 3003 of Pub. L. 104–66","children":[],"tail":", as amended, set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t31/s1113"},"text":"section 1113 of Title 31","children":[],"tail":", Money and Finance. See, also, page 109 of House Document No. 103–7."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was enacted as part of the Mining and Mineral Resources Research Institute Act of 1984, and not as part of the Surface Mining Control and Reclamation Act of 1977 which comprises this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"id60317d9b-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 1224, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/87/tIII/s304"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–87, title III, § 304","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1977-08-03"},"text":"Aug. 3, 1977","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/91/454"},"text":"91 Stat. 454","children":[],"tail":", contained provisions similar to this section covering fiscal years 1978 through 1984."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id60317d9c-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1988—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/483"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–483","children":[],"tail":" inserted “, acting through the Director of the Bureau of Mines,” after “The Secretary”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id60317d9d-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"changeOfName","id":"id60317d9e-3a70-11f1-83b4-f01f82055b58"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Change of Name","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“United States Bureau of Mines” substituted for “Bureau of Mines” in subsec. (a) pursuant to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/285/s10/b"},"text":"section 10(b) of Pub. L. 102–285","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t30/s1"},"text":"section 1 of this title","children":[],"tail":". For provisions relating to closure and transfer of functions of the United States Bureau of Mines, see Transfer of Functions note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t30/s1"},"text":"section 1 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
